def algebra[T[_[_]]]: SqlExpr[T[SqlExpr]] => String = {  
    case ConcatStr(TextExpr(e1), TextExpr(e2))  =>
      s"$e1 || $e2"
    case Avg(e) =>
      s"avg($e)"
    case Count(e) =>
      s"count($e)"
     case Not(BoolExpr(e)) =>
      s"not ($e)"
     case ExprWithAlias(expr, alias) =>
      s"""$expr as "$alias""""
    // ... more cases
}
sealed trait SqlExpr[T]

  final case class ConcatStr[T](a1: T, a2: T)               extends SqlExpr[T]
  final case class Avg[T](v: T)                             extends SqlExpr[T]
  final case class Count[T](v: T)                           extends SqlExpr[T]
  final case class Not[T](a1: T)                            extends SqlExpr[T]
  final case class ExprWithAlias[T](expr: T, alias: String) extends SqlExpr[T]

Manual recursion

def renderManually: SqlExpr => String = {
    case ConcatStr(e1, e2) => s"${renderManually(e1)} || ${renderManually(e2)}"
    case Avg(e) =>   s"avg(${renderManually(e)})"
    case Count(e) => s"count(${renderManually(e)})"
    case Not(e) =>   s"not(${renderManually(e)})"
    case ExprWithAlias(e, alias) => s"${renderManually(e)} as $alias"
}
sealed trait SqlExpr

  final case class ConcatStr(a1: SqlExpr, a2: SqlExpr) extends SqlExpr
  final case class Avg(v: SqlExpr)                     extends SqlExpr
  final case class Count(v: SqlExpr)                   extends SqlExpr
  final case class Not(a1: SqlExpr)                    extends SqlExpr
  final case class ExprWithAlias(expr: SqlExpr, alias: String) extends SqlExpr

Anamorphism

val toBinary: Coalgebra[Expr, Int] = (n: Int) =>
n match {
  case 0 => IntValue(0)
  case 1 => IntValue(1)
  case 2 => IntValue(2)
  case _ if n % 2 == 0 => Multiply(2, n / 2)
  case _ => Sum(1, n - 1)
}
type Coalgebra[F[_], A] = A => F[A]

cataM

def renderQuery: AlgebraM[Either[Error, ?], SqlExpr, String] = {
  case ConcatStr(e1, e2)  =>
    Right(s"$e1 || $e2")
  case Avg(e) =>
    Right(s"avg($e)")
  case Count(e) =>
    Right(s"count($e)")
  case Not(e) =>
    Right(s"not ($e)")
  case ExprWithAlias(expr, "") =>
    Left(Error(s"Incorrect node, alias is empty for expr $expr"))
  case ExprWithAlias(expr, alias) =>
    Right(s"""$expr as "$alias"""")
}
// ...

val queryOrErr: Either[Error, String] = expression.cataM(renderQuery)

    s"$e1Str || $e2Str"

Tagging nodes

val inferType: Algebra[Expr, Cofree[Expr, ExprType]] = {
  case IntValue(v) => Cofree.apply(IntExpr, IntValue(v))
  case DecValue(v) => Cofree.apply(DecExpr, DecValue(v))
  case Sum(a, b)   => Cofree.apply(IntExpr, Sum(a, b))
  case Square(a)   => Cofree.apply(IntExpr, Square(a))
}
// ...
val typedExpr: Cofree[Expr, ExprType] = expr.cata(inferType)

Use catamorphism to add tags and wrap your data in Cofree

Now you can run next cata on a Cofree

val toTypedStr: Algebra[EnvT[ExprType, Expr, ?], String] = {
  case EnvT((tp, IntValue(v))) => s"($v:$tp)"
  case EnvT((tp, DecValue(v))) => s"($v:$tp)"
  case EnvT((tp, Sum(a, b))) => s"(($a + $b):$tp)"
  case EnvT((tp, Square(v))) => s"($v^2 : $tp)"
}
// ...
val rendered = typedExpr.cata(toTypedStr)

transCataT

def optimize(expr: Fix[Expr]): Fix[Expr] = expr.project match {
    case Multiply(a, b) if (a == b) => Square(a)
    case other => other
}
//...

val optimizedExpr: Fix[Expr] = expr.transCataT(optimize)
